  "description": "Ore textures that loop on each other, (kinda like a vanilla-friendly ore borders RP) Now recolored to Barebones!",
  "body": "<h2>Summary</h2>\n<p>My <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/resourcepack/sknsloopyores\">Loopy Ores</a> resource pack has been making its rounds, and as I've been enjoying playing with the <a href=\"https://modrinth.com/resourcepack/bare-bones\">Bare Bones</a> resource pack, I figured I'd make a version of this that's compatible. nearly every ore-type block is changed. (gilded blackstone and netherite are similar but unaffected, as there is nothing I can significantly do to make them like the ores.)</p>\n<h2>Images</h2>\n<h3>All Ores Affected</h3>\n<img src=\"https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/Q1Kx5UGW/images/1b57bcb6d1dced2b6ba1e36aeaade5b62a98386b.png\">\n\n<h3>1.8.9 Version</h3>\n<img src=\"https://cdn.modrinth.com/data/Q1Kx5UGW/images/95d63d46ae6b6666f164e347c14371aeb50913ec.png\">\n<hr>\n<p>If you have any questions, comments, or ideas, please check out the wiki link and post them there.</p>",
